@icy_tools @nansen_ai @raritytools 4. @wgmiio
great tool to aggregate your nft collection and see how much the entirety of your nft collection is worth. you'll also get to see how prices for your nfts have moved over time.

@icy_tools @nansen_ai 3. @raritytools 
if you're going to buy an nft or if you've already one, you'll want to find out how rare it is to determine its value. here you'll get a detailed breakdown of rare traits for a lot of collections and become a smarter buyer/seller. also good to see upcoming nfts.

@icy_tools 2. @nansen_ai 
similar to the last one, step above but more expensive. you can literally get every sales metric ever and even track wallets to see what whales are buying. try it out for a week for 9$, but any more than that and you're dishing ~$100 per month.

1. @icy_tools
one of the most useful free tools if you want to see which collections are hot in the #NFT market right now. you can find out which collections have been minting out the fastest over the last 24 hour, and even 1h. super useful if your strategy is to follow trends.
